Brian Trammell is the author.  libairframe is now maintened by the 
Network Situational Awareness Team at CERT <netsa-help@cert.org>.
The filedaemon and airdaemon utilities in filedaemon.c and
options processing layer in airopt.c were written by Tony Cebzanov
<tonyc@cert.org>.

The filedaemon design pattern as provided by airframe's MIO module
was designed by the AirCERT project team: Roman Danyliw, Sean Levy, and 
Brian Trammell. Other library functions were written to replace functionality 
in libair and libairutil, designed and implemented by Roman Danyliw, Sean Levy,
and Brian Trammell.
